reviews.text:
What a lovely place to chill out! Our 22-month-old enjoyed bouncing in the ball pit and the mushroom castle. We didn't know what food would be served when we came in - the chef designed the menu himself. And the food was great! It was not the main meal large portions but DELICIOUS appetizers and dessert. The staff was friendly and explained things patiently. 

I've always loved the artist Prudence Mak's works. So glad Chocolate Rain Forest Cafe is here!
